<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 92/75/EEC of 22 September 1992 on the indication by labelling and standard product information of the consumption of energy and other resources by household appliances </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 92/75/EM&Uuml; kodumasinate energia ja muude ressursside tarbimise n&auml;itamise kohta m&auml;rgistuses ja &uuml;htses tootekirjelduses 22. september 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas measures should be taken progressively to achieve the internal market by 31 December 1992; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks v&otilde;tta meetmeid siseturu j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliseks rajamiseks 31. detsembriks 1992; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas certain Member States already have their own voluntary schemes for energy labelling and the provision of other energy consumption information for household appliances; whereas one Member State has formally proposed introducing its own compulsory labelling scheme, and other Member States are considering such introduction; whereas the existence of a number of compulsory national schemes would create barriers to intra-Community trade; </inglise>
<eesti> teatavatel liikmesriikidel on juba oma vabatahtlikud s&uuml;steemid, mis k&auml;sitlevad energiam&auml;rgistamist ja teavet kodumasinate energiatarbimise kohta; &uuml;ks liikmesriik on ametlikult teinud ettepaneku kehtestada oma kohustuslik m&auml;rgistamiss&uuml;steem ja teised liikmesriigid kaaluvad selle kehtestamist; mitmete kohustuslike riiklike s&uuml;steemide olemasolu takistaks &uuml;hendusesisest kaubandust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 130r of the Treaty requires prudent and rational utilization of natural resources; whereas the rational use of energy is one of the principal means by which this objective can be achieved and environmental pollution reduced; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepingu artikliga 130r n&auml;hakse ette loodusvarade kaalutletud ja m&otilde;istlik kasutamine; energia m&otilde;istlik kasutamine on &uuml;ks p&otilde;hilisi abin&otilde;usid selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks ja keskkonnareostuse v&auml;hendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the provision of accurate, relevant and comparable information on the specific energy consumption of household appliances may influence the public's choice in favour of those appliances which consume less energy, thus prompting manufacturers to take steps to reduce the consumption of the appliances which they manufacture; whereas it will also, indirectly, encourage the efficient use of these appliances; whereas, in the absence of this information, the operation of market forces alone will fail to promote the rational use of energy for these appliances; </inglise>
<eesti> t&auml;pne, asjakohane ja v&otilde;rreldav teave kodumasinate konkreetse energiatarbimise kohta v&otilde;ib m&otilde;jutada &uuml;ldsust valima v&auml;hem energiat tarbivaid seadmeid, ajendades seel&auml;bi tootjaid v&otilde;tma meetmeid nende toodetavate seadmete energiatarbimise v&auml;hendamiseks; samuti soodustaks see kaudselt k&otilde;nealuste seadmete t&otilde;husat kasutamist; sellise teabe puudumisel ei piisa k&otilde;nealuste seadmete m&otilde;istliku energiakasutuse soodustamiseks ainult turuj&otilde;ududest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas information plays a key role in the operation of market forces and it is therefore necessary to introduce a uniform label for all appliances of the same type, to provide potential purchasers with supplementary standardized information on those appliances' costs in terms of energy and the consumption of other resources and to take measures to ensure that potential purchasers who do not see the appliance displayed, and thus have no opportunity to see the label, are also supplied with this information; </inglise>
<eesti> teabel on turuj&otilde;udude toimimisel keskne koht ja seep&auml;rast tuleb kehtestada k&otilde;ikide sama liiki seadmete jaoks &uuml;htne m&auml;rgistus, mis annab potentsiaalsetele ostjatele standarditud lisateavet k&otilde;nealuste seadmete hindade kohta energia ja muude ressursside tarbimise seisukohast, ja v&otilde;tta meetmeid, et tagada selline teave ka nendele potentsiaalsetele ostjatele, kellel pole v&otilde;imalust seadmeid ja seega ka nende m&auml;rgistust vahetult n&auml;ha; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas to this end the energy consumption of and other information concerning each type of appliance must be measured in accordance with harmonized standards and methods and the application of these standards and methods must be monitored at the marketing stage; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks tuleb iga seadme energiatarbimist ja muud asjakohast teavet m&otilde;&otilde;ta vastavalt &uuml;htlustatud standarditele ja meetoditele ning nende standardite ja meetodite kohaldamist tuleb turustamise k&auml;igus j&auml;lgida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Directive 79/530/EEC (4) sought to promote these aims in the case of household appliances; whereas, however, only one implementing Directive for electric ovens has been adopted and few Member States have introduced this label; whereas it is therefore now necessary to learn from the experience acquired and to strengthen the provisions of that Directive; whereas Directive 79/530/EEC must therefore be replaced and Directive 79/531/EEC (5) applying to those electric ovens should be revised and subsequently integrated into the present scheme; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiiviga 79/530/EM&Uuml; (4) taotleti nende eesm&auml;rkide poole p&uuml;&uuml;dlemist kodumasinate puhul; vastu on v&otilde;etud ainult &uuml;ks elektrilisi k&uuml;psetusahje k&auml;sitlev rakendusdirektiiv ja vaid m&otilde;ned liikmesriigid on sellise m&auml;rgistuse kasutusele v&otilde;tnud; seep&auml;rast tuleb n&uuml;&uuml;d saadud kogemustest &otilde;ppida ja k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi s&auml;tteid t&otilde;hustada; seep&auml;rast tuleb direktiiv 79/530/EM&Uuml; asendada ning k&otilde;nealuste elektriliste k&uuml;psetusahjude suhtes kohaldatav direktiiv 79/531/EM&Uuml; tuleks &uuml;le vaadata ja edaspidi praegusesse s&uuml;steemi integreerida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a completely voluntary scheme would lead to only some appliances being labelled, or supplied with standard product information, with the risk that this might result in confusion for some consumers; whereas the present scheme must therefore ensure that for all the appliances concerned, the energy consumption is indicated by labelling and standard product fiches are provided; </inglise>
<eesti> t&auml;ielikult vabatahtlik s&uuml;steem tooks kaasa olukorra, kus ainult m&otilde;ningad seadmed m&auml;rgistatakse ja tootekirjeldusega varustatakse, mis v&otilde;ib m&otilde;nede tarbijate hulgas segadust tekitada; seep&auml;rast peab praegune s&uuml;steem tagama, et k&otilde;ikide asjaomaste seadmete energiatarbimine m&auml;rgistatakse ja need varustatakse &uuml;htse selgitusega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas household appliances use a wide variety of forms of energy, with electricity and gas being the most important; whereas this Directive must therefore in principle cover appliances using any form of energy; </inglise>
<eesti> kodumasinad kasutavad mitmesuguseid energialiike, millest olulisimad on elekter ja gaas; seep&auml;rast peab k&auml;esolev direktiiv h&otilde;lmama p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt mis tahes energialiiki kasutavaid seadmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Directive 86/594/EEC of 1 December 1986 on airborne noise emitted by household appliances (6) provides for an indication of noise emission to be included on energy labels, where appropriate; whereas provision must therefore be made for the incorporation of any other information and labelling covered by Community schemes; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 1. detsembri 1986. aasta direktiiviga 86/594/EM&Uuml; (kodumasinate poolt tekitatava ja &otilde;hu kaudu leviva m&uuml;ra kohta) (6) n&auml;hakse ette, et vajaduse korral lisatakse energiam&auml;rgistusele ka m&auml;rge m&uuml;ra kohta; seep&auml;rast tuleb ette n&auml;ha ka muu &uuml;henduse s&uuml;steemide kohase teabe ja m&auml;rgistuse lisamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas only those types of appliances whose aggregate energy use is significant and which afford adequate scope for increased efficiency need be included, </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi kohaldatakse ainult selliste seadmete suhtes, mille energia kogukasutus on m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne ja millel on piisavalt potentsiaali energiat&otilde;hususe parandamiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of this Directive is to enable the harmonization of national measures on the publication, particularly by means of labelling and of product information, of information on the consumption of energy and of other essential resources, and additional information concerning certain types of household appliances, thereby allowing consumers to choose more energy-efficient appliances. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on v&otilde;imaldada nende siseriiklike meetmete &uuml;htlustamist, mis k&auml;sitlevad energia ja muude oluliste ressursside tarbimist k&auml;sitleva teabe ja teatavaid kodumasinate liike k&auml;sitleva lisateabe avaldamist eelk&otilde;ige m&auml;rgistamise ja tootekirjelduse kaudu, v&otilde;imaldades &uuml;htlasi tarbijatel valida energiat&otilde;husamaid seadmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall apply to the following types of household appliances, even where these are sold for non-household uses: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmiste kodumasinate liikide suhtes, isegi kui neid m&uuml;&uuml;akse muuks kui majapidamisega seotud otstarbeks: </eesti>
<inglise> - refrigerators, freezers and their combinations, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&uuml;lmikud, s&uuml;gavk&uuml;lmikud ja nende kombinatsioonid, </eesti>
<inglise> - washing machines, driers and their combinations, </inglise>
<eesti> - pesumasinad, kuivatid ja nende kombinatsioonid, </eesti>
<inglise> - dishwashers, </inglise>
<eesti> - n&otilde;udepesumasinad, </eesti>
<inglise> - ovens, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&uuml;psetusahjud, </eesti>
<inglise> - water heaters and hot-water storage appliances, </inglise>
<eesti> - veekuumutid ja kuumaveesalvestid, </eesti>
<inglise> - lighting sources, </inglise>
<eesti> - valgustusseadmed, </eesti>
<inglise> - air-conditioning appliances. </inglise>
<eesti> - kliimaseadmed. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Further types of household appliances may be added to the list in this Article in accordance with Article 9 (b). </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikli loetelule v&otilde;ib lisada muid kodumasinate liike vastavalt artikli 9 punktile b. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall not apply to the rating plate or its equivalent affixed for safety purposes to such appliances. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi ei kohaldata k&otilde;nealustele seadmetele ohutuse tagamiseks kinnitatud nimeplaadi suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> - dealer means a retailer or other person who sells, hires, offers for hire-purchase or displays household appliances to end-users, </inglise>
<eesti> edasim&uuml;&uuml;ja - vahendaja, kes kodumasinaid m&uuml;&uuml;b, annab rendile, j&auml;relmaksuga m&uuml;&uuml;b v&otilde;i l&otilde;pptarbijatele esitleb, </eesti>
<inglise> - supplier means the manufacturer or his authorized representative in the Community or the person who places the product on the Community market, </inglise>
<eesti> tarnija - tootja v&otilde;i tema volitatud esindaja &uuml;henduses v&otilde;i isik, kes toob seadme &uuml;henduse turule, </eesti>
<inglise> - information sheet means a standard table of information relating to the appliance in question, </inglise>
<eesti> teabeleht - k&otilde;nealuse seadmega seotud teavet sisaldav standardtabel, </eesti>
<inglise> - other essential resources means water, chemicals or any other substance consumed by an appliance in normal use, </inglise>
<eesti> muud olulised ressursid - seadme tavap&auml;rase kasutamise korral tarbitav vesi, kemikaalid v&otilde;i muud ained, </eesti>
<inglise> - supplementary information means other information concerning the performance of an appliance, which relates to, or is helpful in evaluating, its use of energy or other essential resources. </inglise>
<eesti> <hi rend="sub"> l </hi> lisateave - muu seadme toimimist k&auml;sitlev teave, mis on seotud seadme energia- v&otilde;i muude oluliste ressursside kasutuse hindamisega v&otilde;i aitab seda hinnata. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> There shall be no obligation to label or to provide fiches in respect of models of appliances of which production has ceased before the relevant implementing directive comes into effect, or second-hand appliances. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;rgistamine v&otilde;i selgitusega varustamine ei ole kohustuslik seadmete nende mudelite puhul, mille tootmine on l&otilde;ppenud enne asjakohase rakendusdirektiivi j&otilde;ustumist, ja kasutatud seadmete puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Information relating to the consumption of electric energy, other forms of energy and other essential resources and supplementary information shall be brought to consumers' attention by means of a fiche and a label related to household appliances offered for sale, hire, hire-purchase or displayed to end-users. </inglise>
<eesti> Tarbijale antakse elektrienergia ja muude energialiikide tarbimist k&auml;sitlevat teavet ja lisateavet m&uuml;&uuml;giks, rendile andmiseks, j&auml;relmaksuga m&uuml;&uuml;giks v&otilde;i l&otilde;pptarbijatele esitlemiseks pakutavate kodumasinatega seotud selgituse ja m&auml;rgistuse abil. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
